                      Wedding wonders                    Looking perfect for perhaps the most perfect occasion in her life is every young girls secret dream. Seeking to make every would-be-brides dream come true is The Telegraph Weddings, an exhibition that promises to provide one-stop matrimony solutions. Back in its fourth edition this year, the show comprises 55 stalls and brings together creations by some of the best designers in the country. Besides showcasing creative talent, the show also provides an important platform to facilitate long-term designer-customer relationships, feels designer Agnimitra Paul. Medhavini Khaitan will have on show a trousseau line for the contemporary, stylish groom. Manoj Diwan will play on the traditional line, while those with a taste for the unconventional can check out the ensembles of Radhika Singhi amp; Sayantan Sarkar Threads, which has on show a collection of Anarkali sherwanis. Other city-based designers who will participate include Tejas Gandhi, Nandita Thirani, Palki, Kishan, Souvik and Aditi and Tres Loudon. Suman Nathwani presents her range of fine lingerie. Saakshi, Gaja Heritage, Mahabir Danwar and Bling, among others, will showcase gold, silver and semi-precious fashion jewellery for brides and grooms. While Crimzon by Sonali Dalwani (Mumbai) provides the right accessories, VLCC, Keya Seth and Roots n Herbs offer beauty solutions. Stalls that offer interesting wedding gift options, provide tips on developing a wedding video or plan honeymoon getaways shall also be a part of the exhibition. Inauguration today at 12 noon.                  Event: An exhibition of wedding costumes, jewellery and accessories When: August 13 - 15; 10 am - 8 pm Where: ITC, The Sonar (Pala)	                    
	ART      August 13 at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture, 3rd floor gallery; 6 pm: The US Consulate General, Calcutta and Birla Academy of Art and Culture host the inauguration of Picturing America, an exhibition which showcases the artistic heritage of the US and offers a unique insight into the character, ideals and aspirations of the country. Organised by the US State Department in partnership with National Endowment for the Humanities in Washington DC, the exhibition comprises 40 framed reproductions of significant American art. Today at 6 pm: Welcome address by Jayshree Mohta, vice chairperson, Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture, Calcutta; at 6.10 pm: Introduction of the exhibit by Chad Cummins, director, American Centre, Calcutta; at 6.15 pm: Remarks of the guest of honor Beth Payne, US Consul General, Calcutta; at 6.25 pm: Address by chief guest Vivek Das, noted photographer; at 6.35 pm: Lighting of the lamp; at 6.40 pm: Exhibition opens to public. The show remains open till August 25 (except Mondays amp; public holidays), 3 pm to 8 pm.     Till August 14 at CIMA Gallery, Sunny Towers (2nd floor), 43 Ashutosh Chowdhury Avenue, 8717 / 2485 8509; 2 pm - 7 pm: Summer Show 2010. Featuring works by Manas Acharya, Akhilesh, Rashmi Bagchi Sarkar, Ramananda Bandyopadhyay, Sumitro Basak, Shipra Bhattacharya, Bhuribai, Tapas Biswas, Sakti Burman, Jayasri Burman, Shreyasi Chatterjee, Jogen Chowdhury, Sougata Das, Chandan Das, Meera Devidayal, Anju Dodiya, Debraj Goswami, Ramendranath Kastha, Bhupen Khakhar, Goutam Khamaru, Bimal Kundu, Subrata Kundu, Paresh Maity, Chittrovanu Mazumdar, Asim Pal, Niranjan Pradhan, Mona Rai, Satyajit Roy, Suhas Roy, Sarbari Roy Chowdhury, Kingshuk Sarkar, Ajit Seal, Shakila, Lalu Prosad Shaw, Shuvaprasanna, Mayank Kumar Shyam, Paramjit Singh, T. Vaikuntam, Yusuf and others.     Till August 14 at Studio 21, 17L Dover Terrace, 6735; 11 am - 7 pm: Monsoon Mix  an exhibition of prints and sculptures. Featuring works by Gauri, Sourav Chatterjee, Sougata Das, Sambaran Das, Goutam Khamaru, Sujit Karmakar, Anup Mondal, Sayak Mitra, Harish Ojha, Sunil Chandra Paul, Anand Prakash, Hemant Rao, Satyadheer Singh and Rahul B. Wagh.     Till August 14 at Galerie 88, 28B Shakespeare Sarani, 2274; 11 am - 7 pm: Art of the Land amp; Land in Art (Part 1)  a total of 80 artworks by 40 artists from Jamini Roy and Hemendranath Majumdar to young artists like Sanjay Bhattacharya and Jyotirmoy De.     Till August 16 at Art Walk, South City Mall; 12 noon - 8 pm: An exhibition of paintings by Subrata Ghosh.     Till August 21 at Rabindranath Tagore Centre, ICCR, Abanindranath Tagore Gallery (2nd floor): Ganges 21  a collection of paintings on Ganga: From Gomukh to Ganga Sagar is the work of eminent Australian artist Kevin Pearsh.     Till August 21 at Ganges Art Gallery, 33A Jatin Das Road, 11 am - 7 pm: In Search of the Exquisite  contemporary miniature art from Pakistan.     Till September 4 (except Sundays) at Experimenter, 2/1 Hindusthan Road, 2289 / 2463 0465; 11 am - 7 pm: This is Unreal, a contemporary art exhibition by Raqs Media Collective, Susanta Mandal and Yamini Nayar.     
	drama      August 13 at Triguna Sen Auditorium, Jadavpur University: Alliance Franaise du Bengale amp; Night and Fog present La Grande Bouffe, a play written and directed by Avisek Arora with Groupe de thtre de lAlliance Franaise. At 3 pm: The Great Feed (English version). At 5 pm: La Grande Bouffe (French version).     August 13 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Aguner Parashmoni (in Bengali), presented by Dolls Theatre as part of Rabindra Utsav, organised by Happenings.     August 13 at Girish Mancha; 6.30 pm: Gandhar presents Kachher Manush, with Debshankar Halder and Bijoylakshmi Barman in the lead. Direction: Gautam Haldar, filmmaker.     August 13 at Sisir Mancha; 7 pm: Rangakarmee presents Rudali. Design amp; direction: Usha Ganguli.     
	PERFORMING ARTS      August 13 at Rabindra Sadan; 5 pm: To mark the launch of the audio CD, Tagores Sampoorna Sanchayita, Kanikanjali presents poetry-reading by Madhabi Mukherjee, Sudipto Mitra and Shilpi Mitra; songs by Pubali Debnath and Monomoy Bhattacharya; and dances by Kohinoor Sen Barat, Kaushik Chakraborty and Kashmira Samanta.     August 13 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar; 7 pm: Rani presents Ki Raagini Baajale, a rare harmony of Tagore songs to be rendered by Shreya Guhathakurta and the associated ragas to be rendered by Hindustani classical vocalist Parthosarathy Desikan.     August 13 at Ankur Hall, P-5 Regent Estate; 5.30 pm: All India Music Featival featuring Rakhi Chakraborty (vocal), Sankar Banerjee (sitar), Fullara Mukherjee (vocal), Maitreyee Chatterjee (vocal) and Mrinal Sen (violin).     August 13 at The Phoenix; 7.30 pm: The Saturday Club pays homage to Tagore through Thy Infinite Gifts, a rendezvous with the Bards creations in music, dance, poetry amp; prose in English and Bengali. Participants: Sounak Chattopadhyay and Sudeshna Basu in songs, Barun Chanda in readings, Bhaskar Raut (choreography of dances), Sohan Bandhapadhyay (enactments) and Debasish Saha (music). Script amp; direction: Sounak Chattopadhyay.     August 13 at Someplace Else, The Park; 8 pm onwards: Celebration of 16 years of Someplace Else with Bertie and Friends (Willie, Suraj, Sooman and Anindya). Also featuring Hip Pocket.     August 13 at Plush, The Astor Hotel; 10 pm onwards: The Night of Blood, revenge and Rave with DJ Deeva amp; B2.     
	EXHIBITION      August 13 - 15 at Ashirbad Hall, Kankurgachi; 10 am - 8 pm: Astha organises Rakhi Mela with a collection of rakhis, gift items, designer saris, suits and bedsheets.     Till August 13 at Rabindranath Tagore Centre, ICCR, Nanadalal Bose Gallery; 11 am - 8 pm: Bharat Soka Gakkai presents Lotus Sutra (considered the highest level of teaching in Buddhist philosophy and which deals with peace and harmonious coexistence), an exhibition of rare artifacts, calligraphic and pictorial representations and replicas of birch bark and palm leaf scrolls.     Till August 14 at 218 AJC Bose Road; 11 am - 7 pm: Bombaim launches Paris in India  The Bungalow label about combining Assam silk, khadi, paisley amp; ikat to create clothes; Idli label (interpretation of tie-dye and screen printing); and Zewar (jewellery collections).     Till August 13 at 16/2 Gariahat Road, 54718; 11 am - 9 pm: Joyitas Selection presents Sharodotsav, an exclusive designer boutique festival of saris, dress material and costume jewellery.     Till August 16 at the Art Gallery of Bhasha Bhavan, National Library; 10 am - 5m: An exhibition on Death in the Literature of Tagore.     
	TALK      August 13 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 6 pm: Swami Atmapriyananda will speak in English on Kena Upanishad.     August 13 at Bidhannagar Ramakrishna Vivekananda Kendra, DD-44 Salt Lake; 6.45 pm: Swami Achyutananda will speak on Sri Sri Ramakrishna Lilaprasanga.     
